criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  To present cognitive aptitude according to the Mental State Mini-Exam (MMSE)

          -  Independent walking, without the use of auxiliary walking devices;

          -  Not participating in other physical intervention research;

          -  Not having undergone physiotherapeutic treatment and not having participated in a
             structured physical activity in the previous month;

          -  Do not present neurological diseases, history of fractures or recent surgeries and
             serious cardiorespiratory diseases.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Failure to attend all stages of evaluation;

          -  They did not complete 80% of the intervention;
